<br>
To me a warrior is meant to be the master of his realm of class. He is the master of direct toe to toe melee combat. He is the master of his weaponry. He is the master of his armour. He gives up a ton of skills and spells which the other classes have just so they can concentrate on becoming master at these things. Therefore in effect what the warrior does do, they do it well...so well that it's above the level of the rest in this regard. Warriors are what we define as a &quot;pure&quot; class, in that they are the closest to perfection in the given class.<br>
<br>
It's akin to the monks being masters of discipline, avoidance and hand to hand, or the rogues being the master of surprise attack and piercing weapons, or rangers being the masters of quivers etc etc.<br>
<br>
Now compare this to what we do have. Warriors aren't really the masters of weaponry are they. Because there is an AC cap they aren't really the masters of armour either. We aren't the masters of taunt and really our damage output is quite low when you compare to rangers, monks and rogues. So in effect in terms of DPS we are a little better off than SK's and Paladins (and many people even debate if thats the case either). Now this doesn't smell much of mastership to me...does it to you? Where the hell has everything gone wrong? Sure warriors take damage well, but then again I was in a raid with my 60 cleric where we were fighting the Statue of Rallos Zek and it was an SK who full on tanked the last 30% of it until it was dead. The SK was surviving the CH cycle quite nicely thank you very much and with NO DEFENSIVE skill to speak of. This clicked something in my head, that same SK was able to strand toe to toe with Statue and could have done so from the beginning of the battle. That for me blew the notion that Warriors are a musthave for the big mobs...or doesn't statue count as a big mob anymore?<br>
<br>
So where is our mastership??? I fail to see it..really...I'm being 100% serious. Where is our mastership for giving up so many utilities, abilities and spells?? Is it in defensive?? Well I really haven't seen the need for defensive that often for it to be 100% needed, esp when the cleric CH chain is working like clockwork. Defensive is a useful tool when you don't have as many clerics as you would like.<br>
<br>
So what seperates the Warriors from the rest?? I can't see it. It's not in DPS. Monks and rogues own DPS. It's not in taunt, since any of the other melee type classes can easily snatch taunt away from us at will. It's not in our armour because of the AC cap which puts everyone on a level playing field after 1250 or so and really we are on the same damage mitigation table as many other melee classes. So what is it? Is it in our HP? Well with NTOV gear monks come mighty close to the HP of a warrior and with a better defensive table they make more efficient use of those HP compared towarriors. Is it on top end raids? Uber boss mobs? Well 99% of the time you spend playing EQ will be levelling or in lesser encounters and if you just so happen to join an uber guild which is capable of facing these top end boss mobs where warriors will become a factor then maybe you might see the value. But what about the rest?? What seperates the rest of the warriors who may not be so fortunate. Where do they stand?? That amount must be in the 90% range?<br>
<br>
It's time warriors were turned into the tanks they were MEANT to be. Get rid of defensive and put them onto a different, improved defense table just like monks are. Put them onto a different offense table so that we have a better ability to taunt via produced damage instead of being a liability compared to the other classes in this regard. Make warriors MASTERS at SOMETHING for crying out loud. I think it's sad that people cry that defensive is the ability that defines warriors from the rest. That's ONE discipline guys, it's not an innate ability. It lasts for 3 minutes and has a reuse timer and you need to wait 55 levels to get it. It doesn't gel with me. Sorry. <p><img src=http://www.animatedgif.net/violent/mrsword_clash_e0.gif>
