If this shield thing goes live without something to improve Warrior damage mitigation, will we even have any role left?  At one point Warriors were essential for the uber mobs, now we don't even have that.<br>
<br>
My suggestions include: <br>
<br>
1)  Giving all Dual Wielders a chance to Block with the offhand weapon and tie the chance of Blocking directly to the Dual Wield skill.  Set it so that a Warlord would have at least a slight advantage over a 60 shield user, with an additional bonus if you have the Ambidexterity skill.<br>
<br>
2)  Do something about the disciplines, if Defensive is too powerful, GET RID OF IT AND GIVE US SOME KIND OF UPGRADE!  Most of our disciplines are just plain useless, the durations are too short or the refresh rate is too long, the effects just aren't good, or a combination of all 3.<br>
<br>
3)  Warrior only damage bonuses!  But what about the precious 1.0:1.2:1.4 ratio, it's sacred???  Well, shamelessly ripping a post that originally appeared on the Glade, from a fight against a 65 mob in Ssra, let's check these ratios...<br>
<br>
60 rogue: 15,524<br>
60 rogue: 13,532<br>
60 monk: 10,822<br>
60 monk: 9,525<br>
60 war 6,028<br>
60 war: 6,142<br>
60 war: 6,880<br>
60 war: 7,539<br>
60 pal: 6,285<br>
60 bst: 1,902<br>
60 rng: 5,434<br>
60 rng: 6,590<br>
60 rng: 4,124<br>
60 bard: 4,033<br>
epic pet: 5,308<br>
mage nuking: 16,033<br>
<br>
I'll be the first to admit that any statistician would say that this is too small of a sample, but it's what I have.  Anyway, the Warriors average damage is about 6.6k, the Monks a bit over 10k, the Rogues 14.5k, now unless my math is hideously bad, that appears to be a 1.0:1.5:2.2  Ummmm 1.0:1.5:2.2 does not equal 1.0:1.2:1.4.  The Rangers were a bit behind but because of the archery restrictions, were forced to melee.  Anyway, my proposal, put Warriors on a separate damage bonus track, something like (level-24)/2 with the offhand weapons receiving one-third of that bonus.  So a Warlord that now has damage bonuses of 11/0 would have 18/6.  The boost in damage output would help in terms of aggro as well as make us a little more valuable in terms of DPS.  It wouldn't restore the obsolete 1.:1.2:1.4 ratio, but it would help.<br>
<br>
3)  Increase the piercing cap to match the other weapon skills.  Ok, this is minor, but come on, is there any reason we can't use a spear as well as a sword?  Any reason at all?<br>
<br>
4)  Make Severilious a spawnable mob.  Sure we can actually fight for one of the tougher pieces of our Epic, but it's kinda hard when 15 minutes after a patch is finished, a manaburn team has nuked him silly and is porting to the Bazaar to make an easy 75k off the Green Scale...<br>
<br>
5)  Add some lesser hateproccing weapons to bridge the gap between those 1% of Warriors in the uber guilds who can take on AoW, Creator, etc and the 99% who will never have access to those weapons but would still like to have a chance of holding aggro as MT rather than being replaced by a Knight who never has to worry about aggro.<br>
