<br>
2-3 months ago i went to DAoC, and when i left EQ the warrior was the top dog in both exp grps and raid situations, noone was complaining then. Yes warriors need aggro weapons to do their job, but that has always been a part of the warrior class.<br>
<br>
Now im back in EQ, and behold: a 33 pages long &quot;warriors suck now&quot; (basically) post ? What happened during these 2-3 months that changed warriors from being top dog to being sub par ? Next to Nothing. The AA skills are the same, the weaponry is the same, no new expansions has come out, monks hasnt been moved to a new defensive table again, paladins and sk's hasnt gained a truckload of new spells...<br>
<br>
Ive known for quite some time that Paladins, Monks and SK's could tank the same mobs that i do, as well as i can without defensive. It doesnt bother me much though, because warriors are still the preferred tanks... as long as having a warrior with defensive gives any sort of advantage on high lvl mobs, there really is no alternative to a warrior. In a normal exp group, the knights and even monks has been preferrable to warriors for a long long time although people may have failed to realize this until just recently.<br>
<br>
That said, i think the warrior is in need of *some* help. Verant has for the longest time failed to give warriors anything, with the reasoning that warriors are the class that other melees are measured by and thus by definition should not be touched. For a while this was the right thing to do, but as the hybrids and other pure melee got &quot;bones&quot; and superior weaponry thrown to them in the name of balance, and then on top of that got balanced (upgraded) again, the warrior lagged behind what Verants (and our) vision of the warrior is supposed to be. As so many before me has said in this thread, the gap closed too much.<br>
<br>
So.. my suggestions has already been said before in this thread several times.. but good things cant be said to often:<br>
<br>
*  Move Warriors to their own, superior to all, defensive table.<br>
* Replace defensive with some non defensive discipline<br>
* Improve Warrior taunt only, so that warriors gain more than &quot;top of hate list + 1&quot; hate from pushing the button. Make it more like &quot;top of hate list + 100&quot;.<br>
* Increase the warrior taunt skill to 255 as it should have been from the start, and make all mobs regardless of flags and mob frenzy tauntable by warriors.<br>
* Change the enraging blow procs to some damage / utility proc with less taunt<br>
<br>
Things id like to see, although it is highly unlikely to ever happen:<br>
<br>
* Dualwielding 2 two handed weapons at reduced efficiency while making us highly vulnerable to attacks (read: taking up to 50% more damage pr hit while wielding 2 twohanders)<br>
* Class AA skill that let us go into berserker frenzy at 50, 60 and 70 % health left<br>
<br>
I dont suspect anyone will read this at page 33 tho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaielmankajiraliege.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aielman KajiraLiege</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/3/02 10:34:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=659>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The State of Warriors in EQ</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Being plate classes, they should be able to absorb hits better than either the chain or leather classes. However, plate armour is bulky and does not lend for a lot mobility to dodge blows thus they have a lower damage avoidance.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's actually completly untrue. You would think plate armor is more bulky and heavier than chain, but this is a common falicy. Since the invention of the blast furnace in the 1200's, plate armor is much much lighter than chain and even leather armor and offers greater mobility than chain. Most of the weight associated with plate armor is actually the padding beneath it.  Having worn both types of armor personally at different renfest battles, I can tell you some authority. Chain weighs a good 2 to 3 times as much as decent plate, is much hotter because of all the leather it's usually sewn to, and is a helluva lot harder to move around in. <br>
<br>
Add in magic armor and this particular point looses some steam. Put it another way...no knight who had any money every wore much chian, and not because of the damage mitigation factor, but because of the weight and mobility issues. Good chain or scale will turn a blade just as effectively as plate, but at the cost of alot of your mobility.<br>
<br>
Good arguement otherwise...<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
